The paper deals with the problem of global function computation in a distributed system, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also proposes a knowledge-based program to solve the problem, which involves reasoning and decision-making, and thus falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves a formal analysis of the problem and its solution, which falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also deals with the construction of spanning trees and leader election, which are topics that fall under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves the optimization of message overhead, which is a topic that falls under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
